text: A wudsie has orange anywhere on its body. It doesn't matter what the creature looks like. If it has any orange on it, it's a wudsie.
Ok thanks. That's helpful. Anything else I should know?
Just that the orange can be anywhere on the creature, including small parts.

Morseth are blue fish. They can be large or small fish. Also, the fish are all striped but the stripe color doesn't matter. The only thing that matters is that they are fish and that they have blue bodies.
Ok got it. Thanks so much.
Kweps are purple and orange. They can be any type of animal, but they must have both purple and orange in their coloring.
OK, got it. Thanks. Could they be a fish too?
Yes, I believe so. They can be any animal. Also, they may have additional colors including purple and orange (for example, a purple and orange bird with a yellow beak would be a kwep).

All creatures with yellow on them are zorbs. However, the birds' yellow beaks don't count. If they have a yellow beak but no other yellow on them, then they are not zorbs. Also, all insects are zorbs regardless of whether they have yellow on them or not.
All birds are luzaks, regardless of their size or coloring. Also, any creature that is colored green in any way is a luzak.
